---
// Shared architecture diagram — used on the home page and the /deep-dives page.
// Self-contained colors (the teal palette) so it renders identically wherever it's
// dropped, regardless of the host page's CSS variables.
---

<figure class="arch">
  <svg viewBox="0 0 760 470" role="img"
       aria-label="millfolio architecture: the frontier model writes a program that runs in an on-device sandbox and reaches only the local inference server and your vault.">
    <defs>
      <marker id="ar" markerWidth="9" markerHeight="9" refX="7" refY="3" orient="auto">
        <path d="M0,0 L7,3 L0,6 Z" fill="#9fb4c2" />
      </marker>
      <marker id="aro" markerWidth="9" markerHeight="9" refX="7" refY="3" orient="auto">
        <path d="M0,0 L7,3 L0,6 Z" fill="#ff7a1c" />
      </marker>
    </defs>
    <!-- frontier model — OUTSIDE the device boundary -->
    <rect class="cloud" x="470" y="8" width="278" height="50" rx="10" />
    <text class="t" x="609" y="29">Frontier model — cloud</text>
    <text class="s" x="609" y="46">untrusted · sees only aliases (file_0, col_2)</text>

    <!-- the on-device boundary: nothing real leaves the Mac -->
    <rect class="mac" x="8" y="74" width="744" height="388" rx="14" />
    <text class="badge" x="24" y="98">Your Mac — your data never leaves it</text>

    <!-- client -->
    <rect class="box" x="34" y="120" width="150" height="58" rx="10" />
    <text class="t" x="109" y="145">browser / iOS</text>
    <text class="s" x="109" y="163">the millfolio app</text>

    <!-- app server :10000 (launchd) -->
    <rect class="box srv" x="270" y="116" width="262" height="66" rx="10" />
    <text class="t" x="401" y="141">App server · :10000</text>
    <text class="s" x="401" y="159">UI · REST · chat WS</text>
    <text class="tag" x="401" y="175">launchd</text>

    <!-- generated program in the sandbox -->
    <rect class="box sand" x="270" y="246" width="262" height="74" rx="10" />
    <text class="t" x="401" y="271">Generated Mojo program</text>
    <text class="s" x="401" y="289">runs in a sandbox —</text>
    <text class="s" x="401" y="305">loopback network only</text>

    <!-- inference server :8000 (launchd) -->
    <rect class="box srv" x="34" y="372" width="258" height="74" rx="10" />
    <text class="t" x="163" y="397">Inference server · :8000</text>
    <text class="s" x="163" y="415">chat + embeddings · on-device GPU</text>
    <text class="tag" x="163" y="431">launchd</text>

    <!-- vault -->
    <rect class="box" x="470" y="372" width="248" height="74" rx="10" />
    <text class="t" x="594" y="397">Your vault</text>
    <text class="s" x="594" y="415">PDF · Word · CSV · notes</text>
    <text class="s" x="594" y="431">+ on-device LanceDB index</text>

    <!-- edges -->
    <line class="e" x1="184" y1="149" x2="266" y2="149" marker-end="url(#ar)" />
    <text class="el" x="225" y="141">HTTPS/WS</text>

    <line class="eo" x1="609" y1="58" x2="430" y2="242" marker-end="url(#aro)" stroke-dasharray="5 4" />
    <text class="elo" x="556" y="150">writes the program</text>
    <text class="elo" x="556" y="166">(aliases only)</text>

    <line class="e" x1="401" y1="182" x2="401" y2="242" marker-end="url(#ar)" />
    <text class="el" x="401" y="218">orchestrate · approval gate</text>

    <line class="eo" x1="330" y1="320" x2="200" y2="368" marker-end="url(#aro)" />
    <text class="elo" x="225" y="345">loopback HTTP</text>
    <text class="elo" x="225" y="360">ask_local · search</text>

    <line class="e" x1="470" y1="320" x2="560" y2="368" marker-end="url(#ar)" />
    <text class="el" x="556" y="346">reads files</text>
  </svg>
  <figcaption>
    One constraint shapes everything: the frontier-written program runs as a
    <strong>separate, sandboxed process</strong> that can reach the network only over
    loopback — so inference is a <strong>local service</strong> it talks to over HTTP, not
    an in-process call. That's why there are two servers (and why they stay two: the app
    restarts without reloading the ~7&nbsp;GB model). Both run under <strong>launchd</strong>.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  /* self-contained palette so the diagram is portable across pages */
  .arch {
    --d-card: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.035);
    --d-line: rgba(159, 180, 194, 0.18);
    --d-ink: #eaf1f6;
    --d-muted: #9fb4c2;
    --d-accent: #ff7a1c;
    --d-accent-lite: #ffb05c;
    margin: 1.8rem 0 0.4rem;
  }
  .arch svg { width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }
  .arch figcaption {
    margin: 0.7rem 0 0; color: var(--d-muted); font-size: 0.92rem; line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .arch figcaption strong { color: var(--d-ink); }
  /* boxes */
  .arch .box { fill: var(--d-card); stroke: var(--d-line); stroke-width: 1; }
  .arch .srv { stroke: rgba(255, 122, 28, 0.5); }
  .arch .sand { stroke: rgba(255, 122, 28, 0.5); stroke-dasharray: 5 4; }
  .arch .mac { fill: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.015); stroke: var(--d-line); stroke-width: 1.5; }
  .arch .cloud { fill: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02); stroke: var(--d-line); stroke-width: 1; stroke-dasharray: 4 4; }
  /* text */
  .arch .t { fill: var(--d-ink); font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; text-anchor: middle; }
  .arch .s { fill: var(--d-muted); font-size: 11.5px; text-anchor: middle; }
  .arch .badge { fill: var(--d-muted); font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .arch .tag {
    fill: var(--d-accent-lite); font-size: 10px; font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; text-anchor: middle;
  }
  /* edges */
  .arch .e { stroke: var(--d-muted); stroke-width: 1.4; opacity: 0.7; }
  .arch .eo { stroke: var(--d-accent); stroke-width: 1.6; }
  .arch .el { fill: var(--d-muted); font-size: 10.5px; text-anchor: middle; }
  .arch .elo { fill: var(--d-accent-lite); font-size: 10.5px; text-anchor: middle; }
</style>
